e Museum Premium Guided Tour | 6 Guests Max | Entry Included\', \'description\': \'Enjoy the Louvre on and exclusive guided tour, making the experience more personal, interactive, and easy to follow. With reserved entry included, your visit starts smoothly as you meet your guide and head into the museum.\\n\\nThis 2.5-hour tour is thoughtfully designed to cover the Louvre’s essential highlights—from world-famous masterpieces like the Mona Lisa, Venus de Milo, and Winged Victory of Samothrace to other key works that give you a broader understanding of the collection.\\n\\nWhat guests appreciate most is the approach: knowledgeable guides who keep things engaging and enjoyable, focusing on stories, context, and clear explanations rather than overwhelming detail. The result is a well-paced visit that helps you experience the Louvre in a way that feels both meaningful and enjoyable—not rushed, and never like a lecture.\', \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Private-Guided-Tour-Louvre-Museum/d479-6353P7?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Bateaux Parisiens Seine River Gourmet Dinner & Sightseeing Cruise\', \'description\': \'Combine a glamorous dinner with sights of the must-see attractions of Paris on this evening sightseeing cruise aboard a modern glass canopy boat down the River Seine. During this relaxing cruise, you are seated at a private table and enjoy a 3-course meal (if you choose the Service Etoile or the Service Decouverte) or a 4-course meal (if you choose the Service Privilčge or the Service Premier). Choose your dishes from an ŕ-la-carte menu at the beginning of the evening and listen to live music while you pass by the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Eiffel Tower, ... and savour the delicious dishes cooked on board by the Bateaux Parisiens Chef and his team.\', \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Seine-River-Cruise-Bateaux-Parisiens-Sightseeing-Cruise-with-Dinner-and-Live-Music/d479-5836DINNERCRUISE?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Versailles Palace and Gardens Tour from Paris\', \'description\': "Are you planning a day trip to Versailles from Paris, but worried about the logistics of getting there and navigating the popular attractions? Let us take care of it for you with our half-day small group tour. With the help of our expert local guide, we\'ll whisk you away to Versailles and get off at the optimal stop. You\'ll enter the palace and have time to explore the stunning palace, gardens, and Trianon Estate. Get the most out of your trip to Versailles and leave the hassle to us!", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Golden-Versailles-Palace-and-Garden-Tour/d479-67584P2?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Louvre Highlights & Mona Lisa Guided Tour with Reserved Access\', \'description\': \'Our Louvre tour offers an unforgettable experience tailored to travelers who want more than just a visit. \\n\\nExpert Local Licensed Guides: Led by passionate art historians who bring the masterpieces to life with engaging stories and insights.\\n\\nCustom Itineraries: See the Louvre’s iconic works like the Mona Lisa and Venus de Milo, plus hidden gems often missed by other tours.\\n\\nSmall Group Sizes: Enjoy a more personal and interactive experience in a limited group size\\n\\nPrivate Tour: Available depending on the tour option selected. Wheelchair accessible. Preferred language available on request with at least 24 hours’ notice\', \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Mona-Lisa-and-Louvre-Treasures-Guided-Skip-the-Line-Experience/d479-5512924P3?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Normandy D-Day Sites & Cemetery Day Trip from Paris with Lunch\', \'description\': "Take a guided day trip from Paris to explore Normandy’s historic D-Day sites. \\n\\nStart at Utah Beach, where American troops first landed, and learn about the strategic planning behind Operation Overlord. Walk along the battle-scarred coastline and hear stories of the soldiers who helped shape history. \\n\\nEnjoy a pre-arranged Norman-style lunch in a charming port town before heading to Pointe du Hoc. Here, U.S. Army Rangers bravely scaled towering cliffs to capture a key German stronghold. The site remains much as it was, with bomb craters and bunkers overlooking the English Channel. \\n\\nNext, visit Omaha Beach, where you\'ll have time to walk along the shore and reflect on one of the war’s fiercest battles. \\n\\nThe day ends at the American Cemetery in Colleville-sur-Mer, where nearly 10,000 soldiers are laid to rest. Stroll through the peaceful grounds and take in the powerful tribute to their sacrifice. \\n\\nThis immersive tour offers a moving and unforgettable look at the events of D-Day.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Normandy-D-Day-Landing-Beaches-Tour-including-Omaha-Beach-Cider-Tasting-and-Lunch/d479-3731NORMANDY?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Early Access Paris Notre Dame Cathedral Walking Tour\', \'description\': "Experience the breathtaking beauty of Notre Dame Cathedral on this expertly guided tour, situated on the historic Île de la Cité—the heart of Paris. Be among the first to witness the stunning restoration of Notre Dame, one of the world\'s most celebrated Gothic masterpieces, now more radiant than ever. Embark on an unforgettable journey to the Île de la Cité, the historical heart of Paris. Few visitors realize that this famous island, cradled by the Seine River, is the very birthplace of Paris. Once the site of Lutetia, a muddy settlement of the Parisi tribes, it evolved into the bustling epicentre of one of the world\'s most beautiful cities. Today, it’s home to some of Paris’s most celebrated landmarks, including the majestic exterior of Notre Dame Cathedral and Sainte-Chapelle.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Best-of-Paris-Notre-Dame-Cathedral-and-Ile-de-la-Cite-Walking-Tour/d479-8954P40?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Paris Big Bus Hop-On Hop-Off Tour with Optional River Cruise\', \'description\': "Experience Paris at your own pace with a 24- or 48-hour hop-on hop-off bus ticket. Ride aboard an open-top double-decker and enjoy panoramic views as you pass iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre, Notre Dame, and the Arc de Triomphe. Hop off at any stop to explore museums, riverside paths, and historic neighborhoods, or stay on board to relax while listening to informative multilingual audio commentary about the city’s culture and history.\\n\\nChoose the duration that suits your plans and easily access highlights including the Champs-Élysées, Trocadéro, and Musée Rodin. For an even richer experience, add a one-hour Seine River cruise departing near the Eiffel Tower, offering beautiful views of Paris’ bridges and monuments. Whether it\'s your first visit or a return trip, this flexible tour provides a simple and scenic way to see the best of Paris.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Big-Bus-Paris-Hop-On-Hop-Off-Tour/d479-6602PARHOHO?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Bateaux Mouches Dinner Cruise on the Seine River in Paris\', \'description\': "Jean Bruel created “Bateaux-Mouches®” in 1949, introducing a novel activity to the Seine and marking the advent of river tourism in Paris.\\nMore than 70 years later, the tradition continues : take a cruise on the Seine and admire the sights of Paris while enjoying a fine dinner !\\nGlide along the river and see the Ville Lumičre from a different angle. Take a seat and relax as the city\'s iconic landmarks flash before your eyes. The large windows give you the best view while a three-course meal (Prestige menu) or four-course meal (Excellence menu) are served.\\nAn evening cruise of almost three hours gives you the chance to see Paris from its most beautiful avenue. The illuminated monuments provide a breathtaking backdrop, while a three-course dinner is served, accompanied by an aperitif and a wine of your choice. Choose the Excellence menu and make the most of this fabulous city at night.\\nAll cruises also feature live music to accompany your Paris dining experience.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Bateaux-Mouches-3-Hour-Seine-River-Cruise-Including-Dinner-and-Live-Music/d479-23561P3?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Giverny Monet’s Home and Gardens Half Day Tour from Paris\', \'description\': "Venture beyond Paris\' city boundaries and get a unique perspective on French art and history on this half-day guided tour of Monet’s exquisite Giverny estate.\\nSee where Claude Monet, the father of Impressionism, lived and worked for almost 43 years. Stroll through Monet’s beloved gardens at your own pace using our self-guided mobile app (download instructions provided on booking confirmation).", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Giverny-with-Monets-House-and-Gardens-Half-Day-Tour-from-Paris/d479-3731P273?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}]\nLast output from code snippet:\nNone'}]}], 'system_instruction': {'parts': [{'text': 'You are an expert assistant who can solve any task using code blobs. You will be given a task to solve as best you can.\nTo do so, you have been given access to a list of tools: these tools are basically Python functions which you can call with code.\nTo solve the task, you must plan forward to proceed in a series of steps, in a cycle of Thought, Code, and Observation sequences.\n\nAt each step, in the \'Thought:\' sequence, you should first explain your reasoning towards solving the task and the tools that you want to use.\nThen in the Code sequence you should write the code in simple Python. The code sequence must be opened with \'<code>\', and closed with \'</code>\'.\nDuring each intermediate step, you can use \'print()\' to save wh