arch)\n</code>\nObservation:\nPope age: "The pope Francis is currently 88 years old."\n\nThought: I know that the pope is 88 years old. Let\'s compute the result using Python code.\n<code>\npope_current_age = 88 ** 0.36\nfinal_answer(pope_current_age)\n</code>\n\nAbove examples were using notional tools that might not exist for you. On top of performing computations in the Python code snippets that you create, you only have access to these tools, behaving like regular python functions:\n<code>\ndef get_tour_info(destination_name: string, start_date: string, end_date: string) -> array:\n    """Gets a list of tour information for a given city and date range.\n\n    Args:\n        destination_name: The destination city.\n        start_date: The start date for the tour search.\n        end_date: The end date for the tour search.\n    """\n\ndef get_crowd_score(review_text: string) -> string:\n    """Reads a review to understand the customers\' feelings and returns a sentiment score\n\n    Args:\n        review_text: The text of the review to analyze.\n    """\n\ndef SearchTool(query: string) -> string:\n    """Searches the web for information related to a query.\n\n    Args:\n        query: The search query.\n    """\n\ndef final_answer(answer: any) -> any:\n    """Provides a final answer to the given problem.\n\n    Args:\n        answer: The final answer to the problem\n    """\n\n</code>\n\nHere are the rules you should always follow to solve your task:\n1. Always provide a \'Thought:\' sequence, and a \'<code>\' sequence ending with \'</code>\', else you will fail.\n2. Use only variables that you have defined!\n3. Always use the right arguments for the tools. DO NOT pass the arguments as a dict as in \'answer = wikipedia_search({\'query\': "What is the place where James Bond lives?"})\', but use the arguments directly as in \'answer = wikipedia_search(query="What is the place where James Bond lives?")\'.\n4. For tools WITHOUT JSON output schema: Take care to not chain too many sequential tool calls in the same code block, as their output format is unpredictable. For instance, a call to wikipedia_search without a JSON output schema has an unpredictable return format, so do not have another tool call that depends on its output in the same block: rather output results with print() to use them in the next block.\n5. For tools WITH JSON output schema: You can confidently chain multiple tool calls and directly access structured output fields in the same code block! When a tool has a JSON output schema, you know exactly what fields and data types to expect, allowing you to write robust code that directly accesses the structured response (e.g., result[\'field_name\']) without needing intermediate print() statements.\n6. Call a tool only when needed, and never re-do a tool call that you previously did with the exact same parameters.\n7. Don\'t name any new variable with the same name as a tool: for instance don\'t name a variable \'final_answer\'.\n8. Never create any notional variables in our code, as having these in your logs will derail you from the true variables.\n9. You can use imports in your code, but only from the following list of modules: [\'collections\', \'datetime\', \'itertools\', \'math\', \'queue\', \'random\', \'re\', \'stat\', \'statistics\', \'time\', \'unicodedata\']\n10. The state persists between code executions: so if in one step you\'ve created variables or imported modules, these will all persist.\n11. Don\'t give up! You\'re in charge of solving the task, not providing directions to solve it.\n\nNow Begin!'}]}, {'role': <MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, 'content': [{'type': 'text', 'text': 'New task:\n\n    Take the user input and change it into a city or country name. If there was a typo, correct it into the most likely city or country. \n    Dates should also be changed into a format of YYYY-MM-DD.\n    Then, use the get_tour_info tool to find tours for that destination. \n    \n    For example:\n    Austin, Texas -> Austin\n    New Yrok -> New York\n    Lnddon, UK -> London\n    \n    Output the resulting URLs from the get_tour_info tool for the destination as a list for python, but remove the characters from the url starting at "?mcid" and after.\n    Destination: Paris\n    Start Date: 2026-10-01\n    End Date: 2026-10-15\n    '}]}, {'role': <MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, 'content': [{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Thought: I\'ll call get_tour_info for destination "Paris" with the given ISO dates and print the raw result so I can inspect its structure. I\'ll store the result in a variable for use in the next step.\n\n<code>\ntours_result = get_tour_info(destination_name="Paris", start_date="2026-10-01", end_date="2026-10-15")\nprint(tours_result)\n</code>\nCalling tools:\n[{\'id\': \'call_1\', \'type\': \'function\', \'function\': {\'name\': \'python_interpreter\', \'arguments\': \'tours_result = get_tour_info(destination_name="Paris", start_date="2026-10-01", end_date="2026-10-15")\\nprint(tours_result)\'}}]'}]}, {'role': <MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, 'content': [{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Observation:\nExecution logs:\n[{\'title\': \'Louvre Museum Masterpieces Guided Tour with Access\', \'description\': "Take a small group or a private (depending on the option you choose) walking tour of the Louvre Museum in Paris and save time by booking ahead. This tour helps you explore the collection of paintings, sculpture, and architecture with an expert local guide. Numbers are limited to a maximum of 20 people on this small group walking tour, ensuring you\'ll receive personalized attention from your guide. Upgrade your ticket for a private tour exclusive to just your group.\\nThis tour was specifically designed to highlight the most famous works of the Louvre Museum. Entering the Louvre through the original Medieval structure from the 12th century, join your guide on a journey from one breathtaking gallery to the next as you travel through time visiting works from 450 BCE through to the 1800s.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Skip-the-Line-Louvre-Museum-Walking-Tour-including-Venus-de-Milo-and-Mona-Lisa/d479-3731LOUVRE?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Louvre Museum Premium Guided Tour | 6 Guests Max | Entry Included\', \'description\': \'Enjoy the Louvre on and exclusive guided tour, making the experience more personal, interactive, and easy to follow. With reserved entry included, your visit starts smoothly as you meet your guide and head into the museum.\\n\\nThis 2.5-hour tour is thoughtfully designed to cover the Louvre’s essential highlights—from world-famous masterpieces like the Mona Lisa, Venus de Milo, and Winged Victory of Samothrace to other key works that give you a broader understanding of the collection.\\n\\nWhat guests appreciate most is the approach: knowledgeable guides who keep things engaging and enjoyable, focusing on stories, context, and clear explanations rather than overwhelming detail. The result is a well-paced visit that helps you experience the Louvre in a way that feels both meaningful and enjoyable—not rushed, and never like a lecture.\', \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Private-Guided-Tour-Louvre-Museum/d479-6353P7?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Bateaux Parisiens Seine River Gourmet Dinner & Sightseeing Cruise\', \'description\': \'Combine a glamorous dinner with sights of the must-see attractions of Paris on this evening sightseeing cruise aboard a modern glass canopy boat down the River Seine. During this relaxing cruise, you are seated at a private table and enjoy a 3-course meal (if you choose the Service Etoile or the Service Decouverte) or a 4-course meal (if you choose the Service Privilčge or the Service Premier). Choose your dishes from an ŕ-la-carte menu at the beginning of the evening and listen to live music while you pass by the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Eiffel Tower, ... and savour the delicious dishes cooked on board by the Bateaux Parisiens Chef and his team.\', \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Seine-River-Cruise-Bateaux-Parisiens-Sightseeing-Cruise-with-Dinner-and-Live-Music/d479-5836DINNERCRUISE?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Versailles Palace and Gardens Tour from Paris\', \'description\': "Are you planning a day trip to Versailles from Paris, but worried about the logistics of getting there and navigating the popular attractions? Let us take care of it for you with our half-day small group tour. With the help of our expert local guide, we\'ll whisk you away to Versailles and get off at the optimal stop. You\'ll enter the palace and have time to explore the stunning palace, gardens, and Trianon Estate. Get the most out of your trip to Versailles and leave the hassle to us!", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Golden-Versailles-Palace-and-Garden-Tour/d479-67584P2?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Louvre Highlights & Mona Lisa Guided Tour with Reserved Access\', \'description\': \'Our Louvre tour offers an unforgettable experience tailored to travelers who want more than just a visit. \\n\\nExpert Local Licensed Guides: Led by passionate art historians who bring the masterpieces to life with engaging stories and insights.\\n\\nCustom Itineraries: See the Louvre’s iconic works like the Mona Lisa and Venus de Milo, plus hidden gems often missed by other tours.\\n\\nSmall Group Sizes: Enjoy a more personal and interactive experience in a limited group size\\n\\nPrivate Tour: Available depending on the tour option selected. Wheelchair accessible. Preferred language available on request with at least 24 hours’ notice\', \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Mona-Lisa-and-Louvre-Treasures-Guided-Skip-the-Line-Experience/d479-5512924P3?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Normandy D-Day Sites & Cemetery Day Trip from Paris with Lunch\', \'description\': "Take a guided day trip from Paris to explore Normandy’s historic D-Day sites. \\n\\nStart at Utah Beach, where American troops first landed, and learn about the strategic planning behind Operation Overlord. Walk along the battle-scarred coastline and hear stories of the soldiers who helped shape history. \\n\\nEnjoy a pre-arranged Norman-style lunch in a charming port town before heading to Pointe du Hoc. Here, U.S. Army Rangers bravely scaled towering cliffs to capture a key German stronghold. The site remains much as it was, with bomb craters and bunkers overlooking the English Channel. \\n\\nNext, visit Omaha Beach, where you\'ll have time to walk along the shore and reflect on one of the war’s fiercest battles. \\n\\nThe day ends at the American Cemetery in Colleville-sur-Mer, where nearly 10,000 soldiers are laid to rest. Stroll through the peaceful grounds and take in the powerful tribute to their sacrifice. \\n\\nThis immersive tour offers a moving and unforgettable look at the events of D-Day.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Normandy-D-Day-Landing-Beaches-Tour-including-Omaha-Beach-Cider-Tasting-and-Lunch/d479-3731NORMANDY?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Early Access Paris Notre Dame Cathedral Walking Tour\', \'description\': "Experience the breathtaking beauty of Notre Dame Cathedral on this expertly guided tour, situated on the historic Île de la Cité—the heart of Paris. Be among the first to witness the stunning restoration of Notre Dame, one of the world\'s most celebrated Gothic masterpieces, now more radiant than ever. Embark on an unforgettable journey to the Île de la Cité, the historical heart of Paris. Few visitors realize that this famous island, cradled by the Seine River, is the very birthplace of Paris. Once the site of Lutetia, a muddy settlement of the Parisi tribes, it evolved into the bustling epicentre of one of the world\'s most beautiful cities. Today, it’s home to some of Paris’s most celebrated landmarks, including the majestic exterior of Notre Dame Cathedral and Sainte-Chapelle.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Best-of-Paris-Notre-Dame-Cathedral-and-Ile-de-la-Cite-Walking-Tour/d479-8954P40?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Paris Big Bus Hop-On Hop-Off Tour with Optional River Cruise\', \'description\': "Experience Paris at your own pace with a 24- or 48-hour hop-on hop-off bus ticket. Ride aboard an open-top double-decker and enjoy panoramic views as you pass iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre, Notre Dame, and the Arc de Triomphe. Hop off at any stop to explore museums, riverside paths, and historic neighborhoods, or stay on board to relax while listening to informative multilingual audio commentary about the city’s culture and history.\\n\\nChoose the duration that suits your plans and easily access highlights including the Champs-Élysées, Trocadéro, and Musée Rodin. For an even richer experience, add a one-hour Seine River cruise departing near the Eiffel Tower, offering beautiful views of Paris’ bridges and monuments. Whether it\'s your first visit or a return trip, this flexible tour provides a simple and scenic way to see the best of Paris.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Big-Bus-Paris-Hop-On-Hop-Off-Tour/d479-6602PARHOHO?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Bateaux Mouches Dinner Cruise on the Seine River in Paris\', \'description\': "Jean Bruel created “Bateaux-Mouches®” in 1949, introducing a novel activity to the Seine and marking the advent of river tourism in Paris.\\nMore than 70 years later, the tradition continues : take a cruise on the Seine and admire the sights of Paris while enjoying a fine dinner !\\nGlide along the river and see the Ville Lumičre from a different angle. Take a seat and relax as the city\'s iconic landmarks flash before your eyes. The large windows give you the best view while a three-course meal (Prestige menu) or four-course meal (Excellence menu) are served.\\nAn evening cruise of almost three hours gives you the chance to see Paris from its most beautiful avenue. The illuminated monuments provide a breathtaking backdrop, while a three-course dinner is served, accompanied by an aperitif and a wine of your choice. Choose the Excellence menu and make the most of this fabulous city at night.\\nAll cruises also feature live music to accompany your Paris dining experience.", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Bateaux-Mouches-3-Hour-Seine-River-Cruise-Including-Dinner-and-Live-Music/d479-23561P3?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}, {\'title\': \'Giverny Monet’s Home and Gardens Half Day Tour from Paris\', \'description\': "Venture beyond Paris\' city boundaries and get a unique perspective on French art and history on this half-day guided tour of Monet’s exquisite Giverny estate.\\nSee where Claude Monet, the father of Impressionism, lived and worked for almost 43 years. Stroll through Monet’s beloved gardens at your own pace using our self-guided mobile app (download instructions provided on booking confirmation).", \'url\': \'https://www.viator.com/tours/Paris/Giverny-with-Monets-House-and-Gardens-Half-Day-Tour-from-Paris/d479-3731P273?mcid=42383&pid=P00294965&medium=api&api_version=2.0\'}]\nLast output from code snippet:\nNone'}]}], model='openai/gpt-5-mini', api_base=None, REDACTED', num_retries=3)[0m
